      "writtenOn": "2021-05-21T00:28:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Very good question. This is a bit tricky here and the reason is that rs.Run.Submission.GetTreeOpen() is false both in the case tree is closed and tree is never checked.\n\n\nI think the semantic here is the tree should be checked if all following conditions match.\n\n * status is WAITING_FOR_SUBMISSION \n * tree is closed in the last check (\n * last check happened before 1 minute ago (so that CV don\u0027t check too often).\n\nTherefore, `(!rs.Run.Submission.GetTreeOpen() \u0026\u0026 rs.Run.Submission.GetLastTreeCheckTime() !\u003d nil)` is used to express \"tree is closed in the last check\".\n\nI\u0027m reformatting the code to make it more obvious.",
      "parentUuid": "e0fff7fd_882eec86",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 50,
